AnCLI is a CLI-first flashcard platform that teaches real-world command-line skills
with spaced repetition. The use must execute an actual shell command in a rootless OCI container
for each card, let the user grade themselves (Again | Hard | Good | Easy), and reschedules with 
the FSRS 4-parameter algorithm.

Usage:
  ancli [command]

Available Commands:
  completion  Generate the autocompletion script for the specified shell
  deck        Manage AnCLI decks
  help        Help about any command
  review      Start a flashcard review session

Flags:
      --config string           config file (default is $HOME/.ancli/ancli.yaml)
      --database-path string    database file path
  -h, --help                    help for ancli
      --log-json                log in JSON format
      --log-level string        log level (debug, info, warn, error) (default "info")
      --sandbox-driver string   sandbox driver (podman, docker) (default "podman")
      --sandbox-network         enable network access for sandbox

Use "ancli [command] --help" for more information about a command.
